title: BI Analist

description:
* Data Engineering
* Data Science
* Data Management


  

**Required Security Clearance:** NATO SECRET  

  

**DUTIES AND ROLE**  

* A Data Engineer is responsible for implementing, building, testing, and maintaining the infrastructure and architecture required for the efficient and reliable processing of various types of data.
* Selected candidate works with Data Analysts, Data Scientists, and other stakeholders to understand the data requirements, identify data sources, and implement the necessary processes to transform and load the data into the target systems.
* Also responsible for ensuring the integrity, availability and security of the data throughout its lifecycle, and for continuously optimizing the data pipelines to meet the evolving business needs.

**SKILL, KNOWLEDGE \& EXPERIENCE**  

* NATO Secret security clearance.
* A minimum requirement of a Bachelor's degree at a nationally recognized/certified University in a related discipline, such as Computer Science, Data Science and Engineering, and post related experience.
* Or exceptionally, the lack of a university degree may be compensated by the demonstration of a candidate's particular abilities or experience that is/are of interest to NCIA, that is, at least 6 years extensive and progressive expertise in duties related to the function of the post.

Experience:  

* Strong understanding of data engineering concepts, including data warehousing, ETL/ELT processes and data governance.
* Experience in planning and maintaining data lakes and pipeline processes, both batch\-wise and (near) real\-time.
* Experience in using of data engineering tools to support development of data science, data analytics and AI applications for both, structured and unstructured, data.
* Experience with monitoring and logging tools to ensure the reliability and performance of data pipelines and AI systems.
* Solid understanding of containerization and orchestration tools such as Docker and Kubernetes.
* Experience with cloud platforms such as AWS, Google Cloud or Azure.
* Solid understanding of good software development principles such as version control, CI/CD, unit/functional testing.
* Strong proficiency in Python for building and integrating various data engineering components.
* Solid understanding of data security best practices, including data encryption, access controls, authentication/authorization mechanisms, and compliance requirements.

company_description: Royal Terberg Group is wereldwijd actief in de ontwikkeling, productie, modificatie en service van speciale voertuigen en systemen voor logistiek en afvalinzameling.
description:
**Risk Analyst**


**Location:** IJsselstein (hybrid work possible)  

**Reports to:** Senior Risk Manager  

**Company:** Terberg Group – 4th generation family business, €1\.5 billion turnover, 40 companies, active in 15\+ countries


**The Opportunity**  

Are you an analytical and curious professional looking to build your career in risk management? As Risk Analyst, you will support the Senior Risk Manager in developing and strengthening the group’s enterprise risk management (ERM) activities.



You will work closely with divisions and business units to gather data, perform analyses, prepare reports, and support the implementation of risk and control processes. This role provides broad exposure across the business and offers strong development opportunities within the risk, audit, and governance field.  

  

**Your Rol****e**  

Risk Analysis \& Assessments


* Support risk assessments across divisions and business units by gathering data, preparing materials, and helping structure outcomes.
* Perform analyses on strategic, operational, financial, and compliance risks, including trend identification and risk prioritization.
* Assist in maintaining and improving the group’s risk registers and dashboards.


Reporting \& Documentation


* Prepare and update risk reports, dashboards, and presentations for the Senior Risk Manager, divisional leadership, and the Board.
* Monitor progress on mitigation actions and follow up with business stakeholders as needed.
* Ensure documentation is accurate, consistent, and aligned with the group’s ERM framework.


Internal Controls \& Process Improvement


* Contribute to the assessment and improvement of internal controls within business units.
* Support the rollout of group\-wide risk management processes, tools, and templates.
* Assist in mapping processes, identifying control gaps, and helping propose improvements.


Compliance \& Audit Support


* Support compliance reviews and internal audit projects, including basic testing, data analysis, and preparation of findings.
* Help coordinate with internal auditors, external auditors, and other stakeholders where needed.


Learning \& Development


* Actively contribute in building expertise in risk management, internal controls, and governance through on\-the\-job learning and training opportunities.
* Become a trusted point of contact for divisions and business units in operational risk questions.  

  

**Your Profile**
* 3–5 years of experience in risk management, internal audit, finance, compliance, or a related analytical role.
* Affinity with industrial, manufacturing, or family business environments.
* Strong analytical and problem‑solving skills, with attention to detail and a natural curiosity.
* Proactive, hands‑on, and comfortable working with diverse stakeholders.
* Experience supporting senior\-level advisory or reporting projects (e.g., governance documentation, control testing, management reporting) and able to translate analysis into practical deliverables.
* Fluency in English is essential; excellent command of Dutch is preferred.


**We offer**


* Base salary ranging: €55\.000 – €71\.000
* Bonus scheme
* 25 vacation days per year
* Hybrid working possibilities (office in IJsselstein and remote)
* Excellent pension plan and collective insurance options
* Opportunities for personal development and training
* A dynamic, entrepreneurial, and supportive work environment


**About Royal Terberg Group**  

Terberg Group is a leading Dutch family business, now in its fourth generation. With over 150 years of history, we have grown into an international organization with more than 40 companies, active in over 15 countries and a turnover of approximately €1\.5 billion. Our headquarters are in IJsselstein.  

What sets us apart is our strong family culture: entrepreneurship, involvement, and reliability are central. We believe in long\-term relationships with our employees, customers, and partners. Innovation and sustainability are at the heart of our strategy; we continuously invest in new technologies and sustainable solutions in specialized vehicle manufacturing, heavy equipment, and industrial services.  

At Terberg, you get the space to grow, take initiative, and make real impact. We work with short lines, in compact teams, and value collaboration and personal development. Our people are energetic, entrepreneurial, and thrive in a hands\-on environment where you build the future together.


**Important Note**  

We give priority to candidates who are currently residing in the Netherlands. While Royal Terberg Group is an IND‑recognized sponsor, for this position we have chosen not to offer relocation support.

  



**Apply \& Contact**  

Interested in this opportunity? Please apply directly via the vacancy link. For questions about the role, you can contact Jan den Hartog at J.d.Hartog@terberg.com.  

Due to GDPR and privacy regulations, we can only process applications submitted through our online vacancy. Please do not send your CV by email.



Recruitment agency disclaimer: Acquisition in response to this vacancy is not appreciated.

title: BI Analist

company_description: Headquartered in Memphis, US, FedEx is a global delivery service company that has changed the way the world moves packages.
description:
* 

  

We have an exciting opportunity for you to join our team as a Senior Analytics Engineer or Lead Analytics Engineer

  

FedEx moves 16 million packages daily. Each interaction generates data that shapes our digital products—from tracking to scheduling, shipping to delivery notifications.


Our Analytics Enablement team transforms this data into reliable, reusable datasets that power decision\-making across Digital Product Insights. We're standardizing transformation practices, building our Single Source of Truth, and scaling analytics capabilities across data domain teams.

**We need Analytics Engineers who can:** Build production\-grade data models. Establish best practices. Scale analytics engineering across our organization.


You'll work within a 1000\+ global team spanning product, design, engineering, and data—based in Memphis and Amsterdam. Your data products will directly impact millions of customers using FedEx digital services.

**The challenge:** Unify teams, technology, and processes to support strategic growth. Build the foundation that makes our analytics teams successful.

**Your role:** Transform raw data into trusted datasets. Bridge technical execution and business needs. Scale data capabilities across Digital Insights.

**Location**
------------


Europe \> Netherlands \> Noord\-Holland \> Hoofddorp

**The job**
-----------


As an Analytics Engineer at FedEx, you are a key member of the data team, specializing in transforming raw data into clean, accurate, and reusable datasets. This role requires a combination of technical expertise and business acumen to seamlessly integrate data into our analytics workflow, facilitating data\-driven decision\-making throughout the organization.


At FedEx, Analytics Engineers are responsible for data curation – translating data needs from stakeholders into architecting, building and maintaining efficient \& reliable data models and pipelines. The role spans three levels of increasing scope and impact:

* **Medior Analytics Engineers** focus on building and maintaining high\-quality data products, working closely with stakeholders to deliver reliable datasets
* **Senior Analytics Engineers** combine hands\-on development with technical leadership, establishing best practices and guiding the analytics engineering community
* **Lead Analytics Engineers** drive strategic direction for analytics engineering, own the technical roadmap, and scale capabilities across the organization


This role reports to the Manager of Analytics Enablement and collaborates closely with Data Platform Engineers, Data Governance Specialists, and analytics teams across Digital Insights.

**Your activities**
-------------------

### **Core Analytics Engineering** **(All levels)**

* Create and maintain high\-quality datasets that meet the analytical needs of stakeholders and end\-users
* Collaborate closely with stakeholders to understand their needs and translate them into actionable requirements for data products
* Utilize data modeling techniques, including dbt, SQL, Parquet, and Delta, to structure data for efficient analysis
* Apply various transformations to ensure data accuracy, including removing inaccuracies or corrupted data and aggregating data items
* Maintain comprehensive data documentation to ensure a common understanding of data definitions and language across the team
* Apply DataOps methodologies, including version control, data unit testing, and continuous integration

### **Technical Leadership \& Standards** **(Senior level)**

* Advise on creating and maintaining high\-quality datasets using dbt and modern data stack best practices
* Document practices using a combination of SharePoint pages, dbt documentation and other internal information capture methods
* Perform technical assessment in the recruitment process and advise on candidate feasibility and fit
* Develop key functionality for the Analytics Engineering community in collaboration with the Platform \& Data Engineering team
* Coordinate processes to acquire and secure Analytics Engineering technology
* Effectively communicate complex technical concepts to non\-technical stakeholders and collaborate closely to understand evolving business requirements
* Partner closely with other engineers and analysts to improve foundational data models and accelerate the productization of data insights

### **Strategic Direction \& Organizational Impact** **(Lead level)**

* Define and own the technical roadmap for Analytics Engineering across Digital Insights
* Establish organization\-wide standards, patterns, and architecture for data transformation and modeling
* Lead cross\-functional initiatives to improve data quality, governance, and analytics capabilities at scale
* Mentor and develop Analytics Engineers across all levels, building team capability and fostering best practices
* Drive strategic decisions on technology selection, platform evolution, and analytics engineering methodology
* Collaborate with stakeholders and cross\-functional teams to identify business opportunities and enhance strategies with automated data solutions
* Represent Analytics Engineering in leadership forums and drive alignment with broader Digital Analytics Strategy (Vector)
* Scale analytics engineering practices across data domain teams and establish communities of practice

**What we are looking for**
---------------------------

### **Experience \& Authority**

**Medior Analytics Engineer:**

* Bachelor's degree with a strong analytical component, including programming, or equivalent experience and skills
* 2\-4 years of experience as a data analyst and/or data engineer
* 1\-2 years of relevant experience in building data products powered by big data
* Proven track record of designing and modeling through the Kimball methodology
* Experience with version control using git and working in a shared codebase

**Senior Analytics Engineer:**

* Bachelor's degree with a strong analytical component (Master's degree preferred)
* 5\-7 years of experience as a data analyst and/or data engineer
* 3\+ years of relevant experience in building data products powered by big data
* Proven experience with dbt (data build tool) in production environments
* Proven track record of designing and developing scalable analytic tools and systems
* Experience being a member of a data enabling team
* Demonstrated ability to mentor and guide other analytics engineers

**Lead Analytics Engineer:**

* Bachelor's degree with a strong analytical component (Master's degree preferred)
* 8\+ years of experience as a data analyst and/or data engineer
* 5\+ years of relevant experience in building data products powered by big data
* Proven experience with dbt (data build tool) in production environments
* Proven track record of establishing analytics engineering standards and practices at organizational level
* Experience leading an analytics engineering team
* Data mesh experience strongly preferred
* Demonstrated ability to drive technical strategy and roadmap

### **Technical Strengths**

**All levels:**

* High proficiency in the modern data stack (e.g., dbt, SQL, Python, Spark, orchestrators) and common data visualization tools (e.g., Power BI, Tableau)
* Familiarity with the fundamentals of Machine Learning and Statistical Inference, as well as data engineering best practices

**Senior and Lead:**

* Deep expertise in data modeling methodologies and ability to architect complex data solutions
* Advanced understanding of DataOps practices, CI/CD pipelines, and analytics engineering workflows
* Experience with platform development and extensibility of analytics engineering tools

### **Ways of Working**

**Medior:**

* Strong communication and collaboration skills coupled with business acumen
* Project management skills with experience in Agile methodologies
* Ability to work independently and deliver high\-quality data products

**Senior:**

* Exceptional communication skills \- able to translate technical concepts for non\-technical stakeholders
* Proven ability to balance hands\-on development with mentoring and community building
* Strong influence skills to drive adoption of best practices

**Lead:**

* Executive communication skills \- able to present technical strategy to leadership
* Demonstrated ability to drive organizational change and build consensus across teams
* Strategic thinking combined with pragmatic execution
* Passionate about building team capability and fostering continuous improvement culture

**Location \& Flexibility**
---------------------------

* **Location:** Hoofddorp, Netherlands (Noord\-Holland)
* **Work arrangement:** 32\-40 hours/week, with 1\-2 days/week on\-site in Hoofddorp
* **Hybrid model:** Flexibility to work remotely while maintaining in\-person collaboration for key architectural decisions and team alignment

**What we offer**
-----------------

* An independent position with lots of responsibility
* Working in a lean, agile environment
* FedEx is one of the worlds most admired companies and trusted brands year after year
* A challenging position in an international, dynamic working environment
* All digital disciplines in one building, so it is easy to collaborate and learn from each other
* Training to get you started and extensive learning resources to further develop your skills
* Tuition Assistance Program (\*applicable for FedEx positions with a permanent contract)
* Employee Assistance Program for you and your family in difficult life situations
* Great career opportunities in a dynamic, international environment

  

Bring your ideas, individuality, and dreams to our global community. Feel good about where you work. Choose your career path \- we’re ready to invest in your development. Join FedEx.

  



  

FedEx was built on a philosophy that puts people first, one we take seriously. We are an equal opportunity employer and we are committed to a diverse and inclusive workforce in which we provide growth opportunities for all

**Our Company**
---------------


FedEx is one of the world's largest express transportation companies and has consistently been selected as one of the top 10 World’s Most Admired Companies by "Fortune" magazine. Every day FedEx delivers for its customers with transportation and business solutions, serving more than 220 countries and territories around the globe. We can serve this global network due to our outstanding team of FedEx team members, who are tasked with making every FedEx experience outstanding.

**Our Philosophy**
------------------


The People\-Service\-Profit philosophy (P\-S\-P) describes the principles that govern every FedEx decision, policy or activity. FedEx takes care of our people; they, in turn, deliver the impeccable service demanded by our customers, who reward us with the profitability necessary to secure our future. The essential element in making the People\-Service\-Profit philosophy such a positive force for the company is where we close the circle, and return these profits back into the business, and invest back in our people. Our success in the industry is attributed to our people. Through our P\-S\-P philosophy, we have a work environment that encourages team members to be innovative in delivering the highest possible quality of service to our customers. We care for their well\-being, and value their contributions to the company.

**Our Culture**
---------------


Our culture is important for many reasons, and we intentionally bring it to life through our behaviors, actions and activities in every part of the world. The FedEx culture and values have been a cornerstone of our success and growth since we began in the early 1970’s. While other companies can copy our systems, infrastructure and processes, our culture makes us unique and is often a differentiating factor as we compete and grow in today’s global marketplace.

* Proven ability to balance hands\-on development with mentoring and community building
* Strong influence skills to drive adoption of best practices

**Lead:**

* Executive communication skills \- able to present technical strategy to leadership
* Demonstrated ability to drive organizational change and build consensus across teams
* Strategic thinking combined with pragmatic execution
* Passionate about building team capability and fostering continuous improvement culture

**Location \& Flexibility**
---------------------------

* **Location:** Hoofddorp, Netherlands (Noord\-Holland)
* **Work arrangement:** 32\-40 hours/week, with 1\-2 days/week on\-site in Hoofddorp
* **Hybrid model:** Flexibility to work remotely while maintaining in\-person collaboration for key architectural decisions and team alignment

**What we offer**
-----------------

* An independent position with lots of responsibility
* Working in a lean, agile environment
* FedEx is one of the worlds most admired companies and trusted brands year after year
* A challenging position in an international, dynamic working environment
* All digital disciplines in one building, so it is easy to collaborate and learn from each other
* Training to get you started and extensive learning resources to further develop your skills
* Tuition Assistance Program (\*applicable for FedEx positions with a permanent contract)
* Employee Assistance Program for you and your family in difficult life situations
* Great career opportunities in a dynamic, international environment

  

Bring your ideas, individuality, and dreams to our global community. Feel good about where you work. Choose your career path \- we’re ready to invest in your development. Join FedEx.

  



  

FedEx was built on a philosophy that puts people first, one we take seriously. We are an equal opportunity employer and we are committed to a diverse and inclusive workforce in which we provide growth opportunities for all

**Our Company**
---------------


FedEx is one of the world's largest express transportation companies and has consistently been selected as one of the top 10 World’s Most Admired Companies by "Fortune" magazine. Every day FedEx delivers for its customers with transportation and business solutions, serving more than 220 countries and territories around the globe. We can serve this global network due to our outstanding team of FedEx team members, who are tasked with making every FedEx experience outstanding.

**Our Philosophy**
------------------


The People\-Service\-Profit philosophy (P\-S\-P) describes the principles that govern every FedEx decision, policy or activity. FedEx takes care of our people; they, in turn, deliver the impeccable service demanded by our customers, who reward us with the profitability necessary to secure our future. The essential element in making the People\-Service\-Profit philosophy such a positive force for the company is where we close the circle, and return these profits back into the business, and invest back in our people. Our success in the industry is attributed to our people. Through our P\-S\-P philosophy, we have a work environment that encourages team members to be innovative in delivering the highest possible quality of service to our customers. We care for their well\-being, and value their contributions to the company.

**Our Culture**
---------------


Our culture is important for many reasons, and we intentionally bring it to life through our behaviors, actions and activities in every part of the world. The FedEx culture and values have been a cornerstone of our success and growth since we began in the early 1970’s. While other companies can copy our systems, infrastructure and processes, our culture makes us unique and is often a differentiating factor as we compete and grow in today’s global marketplace.
title: Senior Analytics Engineer

description:
**Job Summary:**

Chubb Overseas Group (COG) Business Data Quality Program is seeking a highly skilled and experienced COG Business Data Analyst (BDA) to contribute to and support the development and enhancement of our data products and our business data domains.  



As a BDA, you will assist with the identification of data product and domain critical data elements (CDEs). You will document their metadata, undertake data quality assessments, determine the root cause of any data quality issues identified, propose potential solutions and be involved in resolution activities. Working with either the Data Domain Leads or being an intrinsic part of a LATAM, EMEA or APac data squad the BDAs will help ensure that the data programme’s goals are achieved.  



**Responsibilities:**

The purpose of the group is to ensure data quality (completeness, accuracy, timeliness, consistency) is at a sufficient level to enhance the experience and efficiency of the business and make a significant impact on our global product data strategy:


Following the COG Data Quality (5 Step Data Certification Model) and data project frameworks


* Create and maintain Data Catalogues. These catalogues cover all the data elements associated with a data product or the CDEs of a domain. The identification of CDEs is a joint effort with product owners, squad members and SMEs.
* Undertake detailed CDE data quality assessments and form an opinion on the current health of the CDEs. Along with the PO and BA, determine the required DQ thresholds needed for the data product to provide value to the business. Identify and record any issues with the data feeding the products.
* Undertake investigations into DQ issues. Determine potential root causes and propose solutions to resolve the problems.
* Develop and maintain, with the assistance of the of the supporting technology group and the Data Domain Leads, COG wide CDE data quality monitoring and reporting.
* Support data engineering teams during development and testing phase of product development.
* Assist in the prioritization, and Backlog Management of identified DQ issues.
* Contribute to the development and maintenance of COG application landscape documentation.
* Develop a good working knowledge, both UI and supporting data base, of key applications, e.g. S6, Genius, Meridian, UWP
* Coach and mentor other members of the Business Data Quality Group
Assist with BAU process and data changes by providing knowledge and expertise. This work will involve cross\-functional collaboration across all regions.  
* 

Location: This position is open to candidates willing to work remotely or at our Regional Offices, with occasional travel required for meetings and collaboration.


Reporting Lines. This position will report to COG Data Product Owner. Key interfaces are with other domain Data Domain Leads, Head of COG Governance and STP, COG Architect, COG and Regional Product Owners and squads in LATAM, EMEA and APAC.


  
**What you bring**

* Bachelor’s degree in business administration, Computer Science, Engineering, or related field. MBA, advanced degree, or professional qualification preferred. Alternatively, 5\+ years’ experience in business data management in the insurance industry, preferably Chubb, with a proven track record.
* Strong understanding of insurance business processes, including policy administration, claims management, and customer relationship management.
* Analytical mindset with the ability to gather and interpret data to drive product decisions and prioritize initiatives.
* Excellent communication skills with the ability to effectively collaborate with diverse stakeholders including underwriters at all levels of the organization.
* Ability to communicate and present ideas (e.g., business, and technical), or positions in a persuasive manner that build support, agreement, or commitment.
* Collaborative and approachable style to work effectively with a multi\-functional team, multiple departments, and foster an environment of shared responsibility and accountability.
* Experience working with Agile methodologies such as Scrum or Kanban, with a track record of successfully delivering complex business changes and software products.
* Experience in coaching people through complex change and the ability to lead through transition with a solution\-oriented mindset and adaptability.
* Experience in creating environments that encourage and value the opinions of others, and the sharing of information and ideas.

description:
Role Description:
**About Us:** At Booking.com, data drives our decisions. Technology is at our core. And innovation is everywhere. But our company is more than datasets, lines of code or A/B tests. We’re the thrill of the first night in a new place. The excitement of the next morning. The friends you make. The journeys you take. The sights you see. And the food you sample. Through our products, partners and people, we make it easier for everyone to experience the world.

 **About Team:** The PPC team builds and optimizes large‑scale ML models for online bidding across all major search providers, owning one of the industry’s largest performance and auction strategies to keep Booking.com competitive. We run end‑to‑end research‑to‑production cycles—from POCs and modeling to large‑scale A/B testing—driving measurable impact by optimizing auction levers at scale.

 **Role Description:** As a Data Engineer in PPC, you will design, build and operate the data foundations and pipelines that power Booking.com’s performance marketing bidding algorithms across all major search partners at scale. You will own the ingestion, transformation and serving of large‑volume marketing, reservations and auction datasets across our data platforms, ensuring reliability, data quality and governance.


You will work end‑to‑end: partnering with ML engineers, ML scientists, analysts and PPC specialists to understand business problems and translate them into robust data models; developing and maintaining workflows that feed our bidding, reporting and monitoring systems; and evolving shared data tooling and interfaces used across PPC and other marketing teams. This is a hands‑on engineering role with a clear and measurable impact on how we invest our marketing budget and optimize bids at scale.

 **Key Responsibilities \& Duties**


Important aspects of the job can include:

* Own the end\-to\-end design, operation, and governance of Booking.com’s Business Intelligence Platform (Tableau , Snowflake and beyond).
* Lead the full lifecycle of Tableau Server On\-Prem to Tableau Cloud migration: discovery, architecture, planning, execution, testing, cutover, and optimisation.
* Design and evaluate architecture solutions for BI and analytics infrastructure, ensuring scalability, reliability, and compliance with Booking.com’s platform standards.
* Build automation for deployments, monitoring, extracts refresh pipelines, housekeeping, and infra/ops workflows.
* Drive performance tuning and capacity planning to support high\-volume analytics and self\-service BI at scale.
* Act as the primary technical escalation point for Tableau infra and operations, including incident management and root cause analysis.
* Collaborate closely with data engineers, analysts, SREs, and security teams to ensure seamless integrations with data sources, identity systems, and cloud infrastructure.
* Implement and maintain governance frameworks for content lifecycle, permissions, licensing, and cost optimisation.
* Coordinate and mentor two other supporting staff, allocating tasks, reviewing deliverables, and ensuring operational excellence.
* Continuously grow technical and interpersonal skills through hands\-on engineering, knowledge sharing, and participation in internal/external learning opportunities.

**Role Qualifications \& Requirements**


We are looking for driven Data Platform Engineers who enjoy solving complex platform challenges, who take initiative in improving systems, and who believe that high\-quality analytics starts with a strong, reliable platform.


We have found that people who match the following requirements are the ones who fit us best:

* 3\+ years of experience administering and engineering Business Intelligence Applications at scale.
* Hands\-on experience leading a full migration from Tableau On\-Prem to Tableau Cloud (SaaS) is nice to have.
* Strong understanding of enterprise BI architecture, including content governance, permissions, extracts, performance optimisation, and site management.
* Experience with infrastructure operations: networking, load balancing, SSO/SAML, certificates, IAM, security standards.
* Proficiency in automation and scripting (Python, Bash, PowerShell or similar).
* Experience working with public cloud environments (AWS preferred) and orchestration/CI pipelines.
* Strong troubleshooting skills and experience resolving complex platform incidents.
* Experience collaborating with cross\-functional teams and supporting a large user base.
* Ability to navigate ambiguity, take ownership of platform improvements, and drive them to completion.
* Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, IT, or equivalent industry experience.
* Experience managing or coordinating external vendors is a plus.

**Benefits \& Perks: Global Impact, Personal Relevance**

* Annual paid time off and generous paid leave scheme including parental (22\-weeks paid leave), grandparent, bereavement, and care leave.
* Hybrid working including flexible working arrangements, working\-from\-home furniture and ergonomic support, and up to 20 days per year working from abroad (home country).
* A beautiful sustainable HQ Campus in Amsterdam that offers on\-site meals, coffee, and snacks, multi\-faith and breastfeeding rooms at the office.
* Commuting allowance and bike reimbursement scheme.
* Discounts \& Wallet credits to spend on our products, upgrade to Booking.com Genius Level 3, and friends \& family Booking.com discount vouchers.
* Free access to online learning platforms, development and mentorship programs.
* Global Employee Assistance Program, free Headspace membership.


 Diversity, Equity and Inclusion (DEI) at Booking.com:

  

Diversity, Equity \& Inclusion have been a core part of our company culture since day one. This ongoing journey starts with our very own employees, who represent over 140 nationalities and a wide range of ethnic and social backgrounds, genders and sexual orientations.

  

Take it from our Chief People Officer, Paulo Pisano: “At Booking.com, the diversity of our people doesn’t just build an outstanding workplace, it also creates a better and more inclusive travel experience for everyone. Inclusion is at the heart of everything we do. It’s a place where you can make your mark and have a real impact in travel and tech.”

  

We ensure that colleagues with disabilities are provided the adjustments and tools they need to participate in the job application and interview process, to perform crucial job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment.

  

Application Process:

* Let’s go places together: How we Hire
* This role does not come with relocation assistance.


 Booking.com is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. We strive to move well beyond traditional equal opportunity and work to create an environment that allows everyone to thrive.

description:
Role Description:

About Us: At Booking.com, data drives our decisions. Technology is at our core. And innovation is everywhere. But our company is more than datasets, lines of code or A/B tests. We’re the thrill of the first night in a new place. The excitement of the next morning. The friends you encounter. The journeys you take. The sights you see. And the memories you make. Through our products, partners and people, we make it easier for everyone to experience the world.


About the team: The Data \& AI Governance department enables extending the governance theme of policies, standards, processes and technology for governing data and AI to driving excellence in our approach to leveraging secure, trusted, accessible data for data driven decision making through:

* An overarching Data \& AI Policy to include associated standards
* Data \& AI Governance including meta and master data management
* Data \& AI Delivery Governance
* Data \& AI Quality including both technical and business quality measures


This enables the maturity of Data and AI capabilities across Booking.com, unlocking data and algorithms as assets for delivering innovative growth opportunities and cost saving operational efficiencies.

  

Role Description: We are looking for a Data \& AI Governance Senior Specialist to join our Data \& AI Governance organization, working across the Data \& Machine Learning department, as an integral role in the Data \& AI Governance team, on and off shore, as an individual contributor. The Configuration Senior Specialist must have demonstrated experience in metadata management tooling configuration in addition to demonstrated experience in working on large cross\-organizational Data \& AI Governance initiatives. Ideal candidates should have a technical background in Data \& AI Governance Standards \& Frameworks, Data Ownership \& Stewardship, Risk Management, Regulatory Change, and Business Operations and various Data Governance tools. They must be able to thrive and succeed in an entrepreneurial environment, and not be hindered by ambiguity or competing priorities. This means not only being able to develop and drive high\-level strategic initiatives, but can also roll up their sleeves, dig in and help drive change.


This role is a mix of leadership (leading a small virtual team of specialists and analysts) as an individual contributor, and it demands skills as an evangelist and a partner \- at a time where transformation and modernization of our data ecosystem is a company\-wide priority. This role requires a blend of skills and knowledge of data architecture, platform\-specific expertise, and software delivery discipline.


Key Job Responsibilities and Duties:


Data and AI Governance:

* Data Stewardship: Own the ease of use and access for Data Ownership and Stewardship roles and responsibilities across tools, ensuring clear accountability and proper onboarding of data stewards with intuitive user journeys.
* Data \& AI Governance Principles: Apply and enforce Data \& AI Governance principles, processes, policies, and standards to ensure consistent and effective governance practices.
* Regulatory framework mapping: Ensure adherence to Data \& AI regulatory policies, such as GDPR, DMA, SOx, and the EU AI Act, by staying updated on compliance requirements and Technical ability to translate frameworks like the EU AI Act or NIST into configurable "assessments" or "checklists" within the tool.
* Data \& AI Governance Practices: Drive the adoption of Data \& AI Governance capabilities including Data \& AI Literacy, data cataloging, data profiling, metadata management, data classification, data lineage, master data management, and workflows, ensuring robust governance of critical data elements.
* Work with the broader Data \& AI Governance team to ensure the continuous roll out of improvements and evolution of compliance controls to ensure the continual maturity of Data \& AI Practice at Booking.


Configuration Management:

* Metadata Management: Serve as the bridge between Data \& AI Governance SMEs, Architecture, and Engineering to lead the end\-to\-end configuration of metadata environments (e.g., Collibra). You will drive the technical roadmap for metadata schemas, ensuring alignment with organizational standards while identifying and executing continuous improvement opportunities to enhance data discoverability and lineage.
* Mentor and coach configuration team members
* E2E Delivery \& Lifecycle Management: Own the execution of high\-complexity Data \& AI Governance initiatives within an Agile framework. You are responsible for leading the full configuration lifecycle—from design and rigorous testing to reporting and the seamless transition of tooling into Business\-As\-Usual (BAU) operations.
* Methodology \& Governance: Design and implement project governance structures, applying structured change management and project methodologies (PMP/Agile) to ensure efficient delivery and adoption.
* Stakeholder Management: Act as the authoritative point of contact for all metadata management inquiries. You must navigate a complex stakeholder landscape, effectively engaging with cross\-functional working groups and presenting strategic updates to leadership up to the VP level.
* Risk Management: Identify, assess, track and mitigate issues and risks at multiple levels
* Operational Excellence: Expertly leverage the Atlassian suite (Jira/Confluence) to architect delivery workflows, track configuration changes, and maintain transparent documentation. You will ensure output is measurable, visible, and aligned with departmental velocity goals.
* Change Leadership: Champion the department’s change management protocols. You will support and guide your virtual team through technical transitions and organizational shifts, ensuring that new governance processes are adopted smoothly without disrupting the broader data community.


Role Qualifications and Requirements:


Experience Requirements:

* 5\-8 years of relevant technical experience, with 3\+ years focused around Data Governance (or 5\+ years in a broader Data/Analytical role):


	+ SQL Proficiency: Strong ability to query relational databases to validate metadata or troubleshoot integration issues.
	+ SDLC for Governance: Applying "Data Governance as Code" principles—using Git for version control of configuration scripts and managing Test, Staging, and Production environments.
* At least 1\-2 years of experience in metadata management and 1\-2 years managing data teams, including building and growing the team:


	+ Operating Model Configuration: Proficiency in defining and configuring Asset Types, Domains, Communities, and complex relationship mapping.
	+ Workflow Engineering: Ability to design and deploy automated governance workflows (e.g., using BPMN 2\.0, Java, or Groovy) for approvals, issue management, and asset onboarding.
	+ Metamodel Design: Skill in creating logical structures that represent the organization’s data landscape (Business Glossaries, Data Catalogs, and AI Model Registries).
	+ AI Model Metadata Tracking: Understanding how to capture AI\-specific attributes like model versions, training datasets, "fairness" metrics, and accuracy scores.
* Data Governance certification (e.g DAMA, DGI, etc.) or equivalent certification is a plus, though not a requirement
* Self\-driven learner, capable of proactively connect with many other teams to understand the intersection of regulation and data \& AI governance capabilities
* Excellent communication (written and spoken) and stakeholder management skills, with the ability to build strong working relationships with both technical and non\-technical stakeholders.


Benefits \& Perks \- Global Impact, Personal Relevance:

  

Booking.com’s Total Rewards Philosophy is not only about compensation but also about benefits. We offer a competitive compensation and benefits package unique\-to\-Booking.com which include:

* Annual paid time off and generous paid leave scheme including: parent, grandparent, bereavement, and care leave
* Hybrid working including flexible working arrangements, and up to 20 days per year working from abroad (home country)
* Industry leading product discounts \- up to 1400 per year \- for yourself, including automatic Genius Level 3 status and Booking.com wallet credit
* Contributing to a high scale, complex, world renowned product and seeing real\-time impact of your work on millions of travelers worldwide
* Working in a fast\-paced and performance driven culture
* Opportunity to utilize technical expertise, leadership capabilities and entrepreneurial spirit
* Promote and drive impactful and innovative engineering solutions
* Technical, behavioral and interpersonal competence advancement via on\-the\-job opportunities, experimental projects, hackathons, conferences and active community participation


Diversity, Equity and Inclusion (DEI) at Booking.com:

  

Diversity, Equity \& Inclusion have been a core part of our company culture since day one. This ongoing journey starts with our very own employees, who represent over 140 nationalities and a wide range of ethnic and social backgrounds, genders and sexual orientations.

  

Take it from our Chief People Officer, Paulo Pisano: “At Booking.com, the diversity of our people doesn’t just build an outstanding workplace, it also creates a better and more inclusive travel experience for everyone. Inclusion is at the heart of everything we do. It’s a place where you can make your mark and have a real impact in travel and tech.”

  

We ensure that colleagues with disabilities are provided the adjustments and tools they need to participate in the job application and interview process, to perform crucial job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment.

company_description: Bij ABN AMRO hebben we een duidelijke purpose: Banking for better, for generations to come. Samen met onze klanten gaan we de uitdagingen van onze tijd aan en geven we vorm aan de toekomst.
description:
IT Engineer III (Machine Learning) (344170\)**At a glance**
---------------


Are you an enthusiastic machine learning engineer who inspires others to create innovative solutions? Then we need your help, in making ABN AMRO a personal bank in a digital age!


How are you going to shape innovation, advancements, and projects within your department? Our employees get the freedom to grow and experiment. You support and guide them, so they can become the technical experts that contribute to a future\-proof bank. We work hybrid, which means the balance between working from the office and remotely is determined based on agreements within the team to ensure comfort and effectiveness. All\-in\-all, working at ABN AMRO means that you contribute to projects that matter and impact millions of customers! Are you up for the challenge?

**Your job**
------------


In your role as a Machine Learning Engineer, you will:

* Expand the scope of Advanced Analytics and AI, enabling cases that leverage the latest emerging technologies, fostering an innovative environment.
* Work closely with the Data Scientists of the Advanced Analytics \& AI Center of Expertise to design and develop Machine Learning and Generative AI models, also collaborating with data engineers and data analysts.
* Deploy and optimize the AI models that leverage large\-scale data to deliver predictive and analytical capabilities for the AST\&I domains, delivering scalable and efficient solutions.
* Build and maintain end\-to\-end ML pipelines, ensuring model reproducibility, scalability, and monitoring in alignment with best practices for MLOps (feature engineering, model training, evaluation, and deployment in production environments).
* Engage in complex long\-term projects, with focus on continuous delivery in small increments, with possibility of effectively leading and planning the projects to ensure successful outcomes.
* Engage and guide non\-technical stakeholders and team members on Advanced Analytics and GenAI cases.
* Collaborate with multidisciplinary teams and manage different stakeholders.
* You will be part of diverse Agile/Scrum DevOps team and have end\-to\-end responsibility, for developing, managing, and maintaining functionalities in the AST\&I area, which are prioritized by the Product Owner.
* Stay curious and up to date with trends of technologies, advanced analytics, genAI and cloud platforms (Databricks).
**Working environment**
-----------------------


We are a Domain Data Store development team (Microsoft Azure data platform) that support the Analytics Centres of Expertise (CoEs) and create business value from data, by enabling data analytics, data science and reporting within the Data Domains of Accounts, Savings \& Transactions, and Insurances (AST\&I). The AST\&I Data Domains are within the Transaction Banking product unit, which covers a vast portfolio of products: accounts, payment cards, packages, savings, insurances, open banking APIs, trade finance, digital products like Apple Pay/ Google Pay etc. and associated Sales, business \& risk management processes. We contribute significantly to the revenue of the bank by strengthening data driven decision making, also cater to different regulatory and operational topics, and we want to continue and improve on this path to Product Excellence. Our stakeholders apply business intelligence \& (advanced) analytics to explore, research and gather valuable insights; and we provide the data foundation and platform to perform these activities.


Our team has T\-shaped profiles and next to machine learning engineering, you can play different roles like: Subject Matter Experts, use case lead, analytics translator. The domain data store team consists of 15\+ members (Product Owner, Data Engineers \& Data modelers) and are based across the Netherlands and India. We value diversity and inclusion and the team atmosphere is dynamic, open and informal.


We follow agile principles and work on cross grid and cross functional initiatives while collaborating with business experts, business developers, product owners, seniors and leaders – hence providing a golden opportunity for networking and serving as a knowledge haven. We have developed a culture where entrepreneurial spirit, empathy, element of fun and celebrating successes is truly appreciated. We do this by respecting and living bank’s values: Care, Collaboration and Courage!

**Your profile**
----------------

* You're living in the Netherlands. If you live abroad and still apply, we will not consider it.

**Technical skills**

* 5\+ years of experience in machine learning engineering or applied ML with a focus on Azure cloud technologies.
* Proficient in Python (preferably OOP), PySpark and strong experience with ML frameworks such as Scikit\-learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch.
* Hands\-on experience with Databricks platform tools.
* Solid understanding of data preprocessing, feature engineering, and model optimization.
* Experience with ML pipeline orchestration using tools like MLflow, Azure Machine Learning.
* Excellent understanding of evaluation metrics and ML evaluation methods such as A/B testing and cross\-validation.
* Experience with Git and building CI/CD pipelines for ML models, preferably in Azure DevOps/Azure Pipelines.

 **Bonus points**

* Familiarity with Generative AI models and the open\-source frameworks for GenAI such as LangChain.
* Knowledge of vector databases.
* Experience with monitoring and logging ML models in production.
* Knowledge of data governance and compliance for ML use cases.
* Databricks certifications.
* Azure certifications.

 **Soft skills**

* Excellent problem\-solving skills and a proactive approach to identifying and resolving issues.
* Strong and clear communication skills in English (and preferably Dutch).
* Effective stakeholder management, planning, and organizational skills to structure and guide projects toward successful completion.
* Working experience with Scrum/Agile principles.
* Inclination for mentoring junior team members on hard and soft skills.
* Demonstrated ability to work collaboratively in a team environment, fostering a positive and inclusive culture.
* High level of accuracy and attention to detail, ensuring data integrity and the quality of deliverables.
**We are offering**
-------------------


You are given every opportunity and independence to demonstrate your professional expertise and to further develop yourself. We attach great value to personal development and thereby offer you many training and development opportunities. In addition:

* A competitive salary based on a 36\-40 hour working week.
* Benefit budget of 11% that you can decide yourself if you want extra holiday allowances, a lease bike or that you want the budget paid out.
* A solid pension plan.
* An annual public transportation pass or travel budget, depending on the function.
* Personal development budget of EUR 1\.000 per year.
* Banking for better days. These are days you can use for your personal development or on which you can contribute to society.
**Interested?**
---------------


If you want to know more about the position, feel free to reach out to Harold Meijer, harold.meijer@nl.abnamro.com. We would like to get to know you.

**Your Future: Inclusive, Innovative, Sustainable**
---------------------------------------------------

**Disclaimer external recruitment agencies**
